FT  22 FEB 94 / International Company News: Countyglen appoints two new
directors
Countyglen, the Dublin-based property investor, has appointed Ms Sara
Sharpe, with 20 years' experience in the financial sector of the US, and Mr
Daniel Hardie, a Canadian with 25 years' experience in the investment
business, to its main board.
Ms Sharpe and others intend to initiate proceedings, both in Ireland and the
US, against a number of parties including Mr Clayton Love, a director of
Countyglen.
Countyglen has agreed to be joined as a plaintiff in the intended actions.
As a result Mr Clayton Love has been suspended pending the outcome of the
court proceedings.
